This case was reported by a consumer (patient's son) and described the
occurrence of stroke in a 51-year-old female patient who received Belimumab
(Benlysta) for lupus. A physician or other health care professional has not
verified this report.
The patient's past medical history included non-hodgkin's lymphoma.
Concurrent medical conditions included diabetes and lupus. Concurrent
medications included No concurrent medication. 
On January 2014 the patient started Belimumab (unknown), unknown dosing. On
February 2014, the patient ministrokes. At an unknown time after starting
Belimumab the patient experienced stroke, progressive multifocal
leukoencephalopathy and jc virus. The patient was hospitalised. At the time
of reporting, the events were fatal.
The patient died on (b) (6)  from stroke. It is unknown whether an
autopsy was performed.
