FDA - Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS) 
FOIA Case Report Information
Reporter is the son of the patient. Reporter said that he called to give
information about the stroke that killed his mother. His mother started
Benlysta the first week of January 2014. Specific dates not provided. Patient
then had several mini-strokes that led her to a nursing home in February
2014. Specific dates not available. Reporter said that she was in and out of
the hospital several times and the company could contact her physician to get
all the details. Reporter said that his mother also got the PML from the JC
virus. Patient died on (b) (6)  at 1:27 a.m. Reporter was told at the
Hospital, that Benlysta caused his mother's death.